comments: Randle (NYK) firms up in his screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and absorbs the side-to-side contact.
Wade (CLE) brings his arm toward Randle's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs to Randle's front as he starts his drive.
Randle (NYK) is bracing for the contact from Wade (CLE) and releases away from the contact.
Rondo (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in Noel's (NYK) path and does not deliver the contact.
Randle (NYK) turns to follow the ball and incidental contact occurs with Okoro (CLE) as Okoro drifts forward toward the rim during rebounding.
Randle (NYK) moves forward toward Mobley (CLE) and marginal body contact occurs after Mobley picks up his dribble in the lane.
Mobley (CLE) gathers the ball on his right foot and establishes his left foot as his pivot, which he maintains.
Garland (CLE) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before starting his upward shooting motion.
Wade (CLE) cleanly deflects the ball away from Randle (NYK).
Wade (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to New York.
Randle (NYK) briefly grasps Wade's (CLE) jersey and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Rondo (CLE) places his hand momentarily on Quickley's (NYK) side before he removes his hand.
Wade (CLE) brings his left arm forward as he moves toward Randle (NYK) and marginal contact occurs as Randle is passing the ball.
Mobley (CLE) cleanly deflects the ball away from Noel (NYK) and the simultaneous body contact is considered marginal.
Garland (CLE) brings his right arm outward as he boxes out Noel (NYK) and marginal contact occurs to Noel's front as he pursues the rebound.
Grimes (NYK) and Mobley (CLE) jump toward the rim in pursuit of the rebound and marginal body contact occurs as Mobley retrieves the ball.
Quickley (NYK) places his hand momentarily on Rondo's (CLE) hip before he removes his hand.
Noel (NYK) places his hand momentarily on Mobley's (CLE) hip before he removes his hand.
Randle (NYK) brings his arm down and makes contact with Mobley's (CLE) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Rondo (CLE) makes contact with the ball and the part of Barrett's (NYK) hand that is on the ball after Barrett secures the rebound.
Rondo (CLE) moves laterally into Barrett (NYK) and initiates body contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Noel (NYK) and Mobley (CLE) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Noel (NYK) grasps and then quickly releases Mobley's (CLE) jersey during rebounding.
Wade (CLE) brings his left arm forward toward Randle (NYK) and marginal contact occurs to Randle's front as he drives inside the perimeter.
Rondo (CLE) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Barrett (NYK) during the follow-through.

Noel (NYK) jumps forward as he pursues the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Mobley's (CLE) back and head as he secures the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Randle (NYK) commits a take foul on Mobley (CLE).
Barrett (NYK) and Wade (CLE) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Okoro (CLE) and Grimes (NYK) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Stevens (CLE) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
